The paper deals with compressed sensing-based sensor measurements, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on quantization of these measurements, which can be seen as a signal processing problem (cs.SI). The paper also mentions reconstruction of a sparse source signal, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper uses simulations to compare the proposed method with existing methods, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) as simulations often involve processing and analysis of multimedia data.
